metadata.name: Caterpillars #5
metadata.description:
DISCLAIMER : 
I have started coding about 4 months ago and I am not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside. 

This will be kind of a charity project where the PRIMARY SALES will be 
divided as follows:
 - 60 % of primary sales will go to "Askida Fatura" -> https://askidafatura.ibb.gov.tr/
 - 20 % will go to Processing Foundation -> https://processingfoundation.org/
 - 20 % will go to Coding Train -> https://twitter.com/thecodingtrain

"Askida Fatura" is run by Istanbul Municipality and is a campaign that is used for paying the utility bills of the less fortunate living in Istanbul. On average, a couple of tezos pays one bill, and I hope to pay 5 - 10 bills with this.

I will figure out the best way to transfer the amounts later this week and the upcoming weeks, and will provide proof of transfer via my twitter. 

SINCE THIS IS CHARITY, I WILL NOT BE BURNING THE REMAINING EDITIONS!!!

Still, if you dont like what you got ping me and you can get your refund. 

twitter : https://twitter.com/evilnft
fxhash : https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/evilnft
objkt : https://objkt.com/profile/evilnft/created

about Caterpillars,

This is a humble project, does not try to achieve too much, and also wants you to not expect too much from it. 

features : 
 - 8 palettes
 - 2 different origins
 - 5 different characters
 - 6 to 49 sections
 - should be responsive, although I have only tested this on computers...

 press "s" to save a png.

metadata.name: Meta Pyramid #1
metadata.description:
Civilizations in many parts of the world have built pyramids. For thousands of years, the largest structures on Earth were pyramids. Now we can build them with code. 'Meta Pyramids' are created by rendering the code on a virtual paper using a watercolor and vintage-like style.

Features:
- 50 pyramids on water-colored islands
- Vintage-like paper
- 9 different picture frames
- All pyramids has different number of blocks
- Minter royalties %20

Made with Processing4 and layered PNGs

metadata.name: Protein Pelt #399
metadata.description:
An incorrectly placed decimal point led to this pattern. A good friend told me it reminded them of protein structures, I found them to look like animal pelts strewn about.

Each "protein" is made up of 100 pelts, random walking around the canvas from the center. Each "pelt" is made of 5 colors sampled from an array of 84 colors.

Press 's' when in live view to save the image.

metadata.name: Fronteras en abstracto #243
metadata.description:
A place in the abstract, walking in one direction without knowing if you will reach that place. Then, in case you find it, go to the other side before dawn.

It's just a game of words and phrases that have to be given meaning, and we find it on the frontier of something that we don't know what it is.

//

Un lugar en abstracto, caminando en una dirección sin saber si se llega a ese lugar. Luego, en caso de encontrarlo, pasar al otro lado antes del amanecer.

Es solo un juego de palabras y frases a las cuales hay que darles sentido, y lo encontramos en la frontera de algo que no sabemos qué es.

//


Keys

[s] -> download still image (in live view)
[1,2,3,4] Pixel ratios
